# Task: Multi-Constraint Check (Density 5)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: isValid(self, n: int) -> bool

# Objective:
Return True if the integer `n` satisfies ALL of the following 5 independent constraints:
1. n is greater than 2
2. n is not equal to 104
3. n is a multiple of 1
4. n is greater than 8
5. n is not equal to 110
lisp_spec:
(task
 (name "isValid")
 (signature ( (self object) (n int) ) bool)
 (constraints
   (constraint "n must be greater than 2.")
   (constraint "n must not be equal to 104.")
   (constraint "n must be a multiple of 1.")
   (constraint "n must be greater than 8.")
   (constraint "n must not be equal to 110.")
 )
 (goal
   (description "Check if the integer n satisfies all given constraints.")
   (rule "Return True if n meets all constraints, otherwise False.")
   (return "True if n satisfies all constraints, False otherwise.")
 )
)
